  "prompt": "How can India repeal Article 370?",
  "response": "Article 370 of the Indian Constitution granted special autonomy to the region of Jammu and Kashmir. Its repeal has already taken place on August 5, 2019. The process involved the following steps:\n\n1. **Presidential Order:** The President of India issued a Presidential Order (C.O. 272) under Article 370(1) of the Constitution, which superseded the previous Presidential Orders related to Jammu and Kashmir. This order effectively amended Article 367 of the Constitution, making the provisions of the Indian Constitution applicable to Jammu and Kashmir.\n\n2. **Resolution in Parliament:** The Home Minister introduced a resolution in the Parliament to recommend that Article 370 be declared inoperative. The resolution was passed in both houses of Parliament (Lok Sabha and Rajya Sabha).\n\n3. **Constitution (Application to Jammu and Kashmir) Order, 2019:** The Presidential Order made several changes, including that all provisions of the Indian Constitution would now apply to Jammu and Kashmir, effectively nullifying the special status conferred by Article 370.\n\n4. **Reorganization Act:** The Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization Act, 2019 was passed, which bifurcated the state into two Union Territories - Jammu & Kashmir, and Ladakh. This act laid the groundwork for administrative changes following the repeal of Article 370.\n\nTo repeal Article 370, the government utilized the presidential power under Article 370 itself, along with legislative support, thereby transforming the constitutional and administrative status of Jammu and Kashmir.",
